AccountContactPostCreateAsync
	•	Runs when: An Account–Contact relationship is created
	•	Stage: Post-Operation (Async)

What it does:
	•	When a new Account–Contact relation is created:
	•	Adds the Contact to the Account’s team
	•	Aligns the Contact’s access with the Account automatically

⸻

AccountContactPostUpdateAsync
	•	Runs when: An Account–Contact relationship is updated
	•	Stage: Post-Operation (Async)

What it does:
	•	When the relationship is updated (including status changes):
	•	Adjusts the Contact’s access in the Account’s team
	•	If the relationship becomes inactive, the Contact’s access is revoked

⸻

AccountContactPostDeleteSync
	•	Runs when: An Account–Contact relationship is deleted
	•	Stage: Post-Operation (Sync)

What it does:
	•	Immediately removes the Contact’s access from the Account’s team when the relationship is deleted
